This paper deals with the performance analysis of wireless communication networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses game theory (cs.GT) to model the system and evaluate the proposed approach. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a Markov chain to model the system, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM) due to the use of ZigZag decoding.
